Into a 50 mL three-necked round-bottom flask was added 4-Bromobenzaldehyde (1 mmol, 185 mg), 9-Phenyl-9H-carbazol-3-ylboronic acid (1.5 mmol, 222 mg), Pd(PPh3)4 (0.01 mmol, 15 mg), tetrabutylammonium tribromide (0.05 mmol, 15 mg), K2CO3 (6.25 mmol, 863 mg), 10 mL toluene and 2.5 mL water. The flask was vacuumed and purged with nitrogen three times and followed by refluxing at 110 °C overnight under N2 atmosphere. After the mixture cooled down to room temperature, it was extracted with DCM, washed with distilled water several times and dried with anhydrous magnesium sulfate. The crude product was purified by silica column chromatography to give 4′-vinyl-[1,1′-biphenyl]-4-carbaldehyde (compound 1, C15H12O) with the yield of 76.8%. (Fig. S1)·1H NMR (600 MHz, CDCl

                           3
                        ) δ 10.05 (s, 1H), 7.95 (d, J = 12.0 Hz, 2H), 7.76 (d, J = 12.0 Hz, 2H), 7.62 (d, J = 12.0 Hz, 2H), 7.52 (d, J = 12.0 Hz, 2H), 6.81–6.73 (m, 1H), 5.84 (d, J = 30.0 Hz, 1H), 5.32 (d, J = 18.0 Hz, 1H) (Fig. S2).

To a solution of compound 1 (1 mmol, 208 mg) in 15 mL ethanol were added 2-acetylpyridine (2 mmol, 0.25 mL) and potassium hydroxide (1 mmol, 75 mg). After stirring 3 h at room temperature, ammonium hydroxide (1.25 mmol, 1.5 mL) was added and stirring was continued overnight. The resulting precipitate was filtered and washed with ethanol to produce 4'-(4′-vinyl-[1,1′-biphenyl]-4-yl)-2,2':6′,2″-terpyridine (ligand L, C29H21N3) as a yellow powder with the yield of 63.6%. 1H NMR (600 MHz, CDCl

                           3
                        ) δ 8.87 (s, 1H), 8.80 (d, J = 6.0 Hz, 2H), 8.75 (d, J = 6.0 Hz, 1H), 8.39 (d, J = 12.0 Hz, 1H), 8.06 (d, J = 6.0 Hz, 2H), 7.96 (t, J = 6.0 Hz, 2H), 7.79 (d, J = 12.0 Hz, 2H), 7.69 (d, J = 6.0 Hz, 2H), 7.56 (d, J = 6.0 Hz, 2H), 7.46–7.41 (m, 1H), 6.83–6.79 (m, 1H), 5.86 (d, J = 18.0 Hz, 1H), 5.33 (d, J = 12.0 Hz, 1H) (Fig. S3). HR-MS (ESI): (C24H19N3O) m/z: calculated for [M]: 411.1735. Found [M+H]+: 412.1813 (Fig. S4).
